column2: Custom Data format allows extension authors to extend VS Code's HTML language support.
Custom Data format provides language support for CSS entities defined in custom data files.
The `package.json` of a VS Code extension should include `contributes.html.customData` and `contributes.css.customData` to use custom data.
Custom Data format provides auto-completion and hover information for HTML/CSS entities defined in custom data files.
The custom-data-sample can be found in [microsoft/vscode-extension-samples](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-extension-samples).
